<h3>2. Lavender — Email Writing AI</h3>
<div class="guide-tool-card">
  <div class="guide-tool-header">
    <div>
      <div class="guide-tool-rank">Best for follow-up and multi-threading emails</div>
      <h3 class="guide-tool-name">Lavender</h3>
      <p class="guide-tool-tagline">AI email coach that improves reply rates on follow-up and multi-threading outreach</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="guide-tool-body">
    <p>Lavender is primarily marketed to SDRs for cold outreach, but its value for AEs is equally strong — and often overlooked. The most common AE use case is not cold prospecting but follow-up emails after demos, multi-threading into new stakeholders at active accounts, and re-engagement emails when deals go dark.</p>
    <p>Lavender's email scoring and personalization suggestions work on any email, not just cold outreach. AEs who use Lavender for post-demo follow-up and multi-threading emails consistently report 20–35% improvement in reply rates on these critical touchpoints — the emails that most directly affect deal velocity.</p>
    <h4>What AEs actually use it for:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Post-demo follow-up emails — Lavender scores the email and suggests improvements before sending</li>
      <li>Multi-threading into new stakeholders — personalization suggestions based on LinkedIn data</li>
      <li>Re-engagement emails for stalled deals — Lavender's "email coach" mode is particularly useful here</li>
      <li>Executive outreach — the brevity and clarity scoring helps AEs write emails that busy executives actually read</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Honest limitations for AEs:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Works best with Gmail — Outlook integration is functional but less seamless</li>
      <li>Personalization suggestions require LinkedIn data — less useful for contacts with minimal LinkedIn presence</li>
      <li>$29/month individual plan is reasonable, but team plans add up</li>
    </ul>
