<h2>What to Ignore</h2>
<p>Several categories of AI sales tools are heavily marketed to AEs but deliver limited value in practice:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>AI proposal generators</strong> — the proposals they produce require so much editing that writing from scratch is often faster. The exception is tools deeply integrated with your CRM that can pull deal-specific data automatically.</li>
  <li><strong>AI meeting schedulers beyond basic calendar links</strong> — HubSpot's meeting link or Calendly solves 95% of scheduling friction. Complex AI scheduling tools add cost without proportional value.</li>
  <li><strong>Generic "AI sales assistant" chatbots</strong> — tools that promise to answer any sales question with AI are solving a problem that doesn't exist for most AEs. The specific, workflow-integrated AI in Gong, Lavender, and Clay delivers far more value than general-purpose AI assistants.</li>
</ul>

